<div class="row justify-content-center my-4 my-md-5">
    <div class="col-12 col-lg-10 col-xl-9">
        <div class="card shadow-sm">
            <div class="card-body p-4 p-md-5">

                <p>
                    Schedule Master (“we”, “our”, or “us”) respects your privacy and is committed to protecting it.
                    This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect your information when you use our
                    website and mobile application (collectively, the “Service”).
                </p>

                <p>
                    By using Schedule Master, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this
                    Privacy Policy.
                </p>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 class="h5">1. Information We Collect</h2>
                <p>We collect only the information necessary to provide and improve our Service.</p>

                <h3 class="h6 mt-3">1.1 Personal Information</h3>
                <p>When you create an account, we may collect:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Name or username</li>
                    <li>Email address</li>
                    <li>User account identifiers (such as an internal user ID)</li>
                </ul>
                <p>This information is used solely for account creation, authentication, and account management.</p>

                <h3 class="h6 mt-3">1.2 User-Generated Content</h3>
                <p>When using Schedule Master, you may create and store:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Calendar events</li>
                    <li>Event titles, descriptions, start and end times, and colors</li>
                </ul>
                <p>This data is created by you and stored to provide the core functionality of the Service.</p>

                <h3 class="h6 mt-3">1.3 App and Usage Data</h3>
                <p>We may automatically collect limited technical data such as:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>App interactions</li>
                    <li>Session information</li>
                    <li>Log data (e.g., access times, error logs)</li>
                </ul>
                <p>This information is used to ensure security, maintain performance, and improve reliability.</p>

                <h3 class="h6 mt-3">1.4 Device and Session Information</h3>
                <p>We may use cookies, authentication tokens, or similar technologies to:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Keep you signed in</li>
                    <li>Protect your account</li>
                    <li>Prevent unauthorized access</li>
                </ul>
                <p>We do not collect device identifiers such as IMEI numbers or advertising IDs.</p>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 class="h5">2. Information We Do Not Collect</h2>
                <p>We do not collect or process:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Precise or approximate location data</li>
                    <li>Financial or payment information</li>
                    <li>Health or fitness data</li>
                    <li>Contacts or address book data</li>
                    <li>Photos, videos, audio recordings, or files</li>
                    <li>SMS, MMS, or email message content</li>
                    <li>Sensitive personal data such as race, ethnicity, religious beliefs, political beliefs, or sexual orientation</li>
                </ul>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 class="h5">3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
                <p>We use collected information only to:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Provide and operate the Service</li>
                    <li>Create and manage user accounts</li>
                    <li>Store and display your calendar events</li>
                    <li>Improve app functionality and security</li>
                    <li>Respond to support requests</li>
                </ul>
                <p>We do not use your data for advertising or marketing purposes.</p>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 class="h5">4. Data Sharing</h2>
                <p>We do not sell, rent, or share your personal data with third parties.</p>
                <p>
                    Your information may be processed by trusted service providers only when necessary to operate the Service
                    (such as hosting or authentication services), and only under strict confidentiality and security obligations.
                </p>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 class="h5">5. Data Security</h2>
                <p>
                    We take reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your information against unauthorized
                    access, loss, or misuse. However, no method of transmission or storage is 100% secure, and we cannot
                    guarantee absolute security.
                </p>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 class="h5">6. Data Retention</h2>
                <p>
                    We retain your personal information and calendar data only for as long as your account remains active or as
                    necessary to provide the Service. You may request deletion of your account and associated data at any time.
                </p>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 class="h5">7. Your Rights</h2>
                <p>
                    Depending on your location, you may have the right to access your personal data, request correction or
                    deletion of your data, or withdraw consent by deleting your account.
                </p>
                <p>To exercise these rights, please contact us using the information below.</p>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 class="h5">8. Children’s Privacy</h2>
                <p>
                    Schedule Master may be used by children under the age of 13 with the consent and supervision of a parent or legal guardian. We encourage parents and guardians to be involved in their child’s use of the site and to monitor their activity.
                </p>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 class="h5">9. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
                <p>
                    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an
                    updated effective date. Continued use of the Service after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated
                    policy.
                </p>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 class="h5">10. Contact Information</h2>
                <p>If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or your data, you may contact us at:</p>
                <div class="border rounded p-3 bg-white">
                    <div><strong>Email:</strong> <span>support@@repocove.com</span></div>
                    <div><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://schedule1master.bsite.net/" class="link-primary">https://schedule1master.bsite.net</a></div>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-center text-muted mt-4 mb-0">
            <small>© <span id="year"></span> Schedule Master. All rights reserved.</small>
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
